There is something wrong with TRIM policy ,  as of now we have set it to "Block and Report  "  and if a user Try to upload any file containing sensitive information get block and user is getting Pop message on their screen  ( see pic below )  while using those 3 apps . But when they just simply type the sensitive content on their Browser ( chrome )  and process it ( like comment box )  ,  they able to do it  and EPP console don't generate any Alert as well .

I have tested with Poonum and Daniel , both having same issue .

Just a reminder that Poonum just  got Fresh copy of Client installed  on her Laptop .  Please reply with your remote session availability if needed or Suggest if we need to do additional configurations on the console side . Thanks

Hey Lucinda,

The transparent proxy is exactly that, a local proxy that is used by the dpi function to check packets for restricted content. This way we catch restricted content even before they try to leave the computer.
As for the VPN connection, that is something we had to introduce since Sonoma changed the way security is handled and that was the only workaround to be able to set the proxy. This has no actual use once the proxy is enabled, and it might even be disabled under regular work conditions.
If you are not part of a group that enabled DPI, this is not needed or set.
Let me know if you have follow-up questions.

Thank you,
Eduard Nut
Technical Support Engineer

Hey Lucinda,

The transparent proxy is exactly that, a local proxy that is used by the dpi function to check packets for restricted content. This way we catch restricted content even before they try to leave the computer.
As for the VPN connection, that is something we had to introduce since Sonoma changed the way security is handled and that was the only workaround to be able to set the proxy. This has no actual use once the proxy is enabled, and it might even be disabled under regular work conditions.
If you are not part of a group that enabled DPI, this is not needed or set.
Let me know if you have follow-up questions.

Thank you,
Eduard Nut

Hey Lucinda,

The transparent proxy is exactly that, a local proxy that is used by the dpi function to check packets for restricted content. This way we catch restricted content even before they try to leave the computer.
As for the VPN connection, that is something we had to introduce since Sonoma changed the way security is handled and that was the only workaround to be able to set the proxy. This has no actual use once the proxy is enabled, and it might even be disabled under regular work conditions.
If you are not part of a group that enabled DPI, this is not needed or set.
Let me know if you have follow-up questions.

Thank you,
Eduard Nut
Technical Support Engineer

Hey Lucinda,

The transparent proxy is exactly that, a local proxy that is used by the dpi function to check packets for restricted content. This way we catch restricted content even before they try to leave the computer.
As for the VPN connection, that is something we had to introduce since Sonoma changed the way security is handled and that was the only workaround to be able to set the proxy. This has no actual use once the proxy is enabled, and it might even be disabled under regular work conditions.
If you are not part of a group that enabled DPI, this is not needed or set.
Let me know if you have follow-up questions.

Thank you,

Hey Lucinda,

The transparent proxy is exactly that, a local proxy that is used by the dpi function to check packets for restricted content. This way we catch restricted content even before they try to leave the computer.
As for the VPN connection, that is something we had to introduce since Sonoma changed the way security is handled and that was the only workaround to be able to set the proxy. This has no actual use once the proxy is enabled, and it might even be disabled under regular work conditions.
If you are not part of a group that enabled DPI, this is not needed or set.
Let me know if you have follow-up questions.

Thank you,
Eduard Nut

Hey Lucinda,

The transparent proxy is exactly that, a local proxy that is used by the dpi function to check packets for restricted content. This way we catch restricted content even before they try to leave the computer.
As for the VPN connection, that is something we had to introduce since Sonoma changed the way security is handled and that was the only workaround to be able to set the proxy. This has no actual use once the proxy is enabled, and it might even be disabled under regular work conditions.
If you are not part of a group that enabled DPI, this is not needed or set.
Let me know if you have follow-up questions.

Thank you,
Eduard Nut
Technical Support Engineer
